  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Preheat the oven to 160&deg;C/ 140&deg;C (fan)/ 325&deg;F/ Gas 3</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel&nbsp;and finely chop the <strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Strip the<strong> rosemary</strong> <strong>leaves</strong> from their stalks and chop finely</p>\r\n<p>Grate the <strong>Italian hard&nbsp;cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel the <strong>parsnips</strong></p>\r\n<p>Continue to peel lengths off&nbsp;the parsnip until you end up with a pile of <strong>parsnip 'ribbons'</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once you can't peel any further, chop the remaining parsnip&nbsp;core&nbsp;into bite-size&nbsp;chunks</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>parsnip ribbons</strong>, <strong>cumin seeds</strong> and a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>olive oil</strong> to a bowl and give it a good old mix up</p>\r\n<p>Line a baking&nbsp;tray with some <strong>baking paper</strong> and&nbsp;add the <strong>parsnip ribbons</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tip: make sure they don't overlap as they won't crisp properly</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put the tray in the oven for 15 min or until the parsnip ribbons are browned at the edges</p>\r\n<p>Once done, remove the tray from the oven and place them on a piece of kitchen paper to cool - these are your <strong>parsnip crisps</strong></p>\r\n<p>Season&nbsp;generously with<strong> salt</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the<strong> vegetable&nbsp;stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;in 750ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.5L]&nbsp;</span><strong>boiled water</strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a large knob of<strong> butter</strong>&nbsp;over a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>parsnip </strong><strong>chunks&nbsp;</strong>and<strong>&nbsp;chopped onion</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until the parsnip has coloured slightly</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>arborio rice</strong> and<strong>&nbsp;chopped rosemary</strong> to the pan and stir through for 2 min</p>\r\n<p>Add&nbsp;1/3&nbsp;of the stock to the rice and stir continuously with a wooden spoon until the stock is absorbed</p>\r\n<p>Continue to add the stock, a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 20-25 min&nbsp;or until all the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/172_step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, remove the pan from the heat and stir in the <strong>grated cheese</strong></p>\r\n<p>Taste for seasoning, adding more <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> if needed</p>\r\n<p>Serve&nbsp;and garnish with the <strong>parsnip crisps</strong> and drizzle with <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
